# MorScan - local development environment
#
# Copy to .env for `wrangler dev`. NEVER commit .env.
# In production these are set as Worker secrets:
#   wrangler secret put <NAME>
#
# MORSCAN_JWT_SECRET - UI session signing. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# MORSCAN_MNEMONIC   - BIP39 mnemonic for Ed25519 provenance/snapshot signing.
#                     Must be a REAL 12/24-word mnemonic, not random hex.
# MORSCAN_DEMO_KEY   - optional full-access demo key embedded in the UI.
# MORSCAN_ADMIN_KEY_IDS - comma-separated api_keys ids granted admin bypass for
#                     /sync/*, /mor/v1/bq/*, and /admin/* (isAdminAuth). Use a
#                     wallet key id like wallet:0xYourAddr. Optional; `admin` is
#                     always an admin. Never put a real value in the repo.
# ALCHEMY_FALLBACK_URL - optional Alchemy RPC URL for the block-receipt projector.
# D1_DAILY_READ_BUDGET - non-secret override (normally set in wrangler.toml
#                     [vars]). Approx D1 rows-read/day before the heavy uncached
#                     /mor/v1 endpoints shed to a 503 (Free-plan backstop).
#                     Default 4000000, under the ~5M/day free limit. Lower it to
#                     force-test the guard. See src/utils/d1-budget.ts.
#
# Non-secret config (PUBLIC_BASE_URL, WARRANT_KEY_REGISTRY_URL,
# SNAPSHOT_PUBLIC_HOST, SNAPSHOT_SIGNER_KEY_ID, D1_DAILY_READ_BUDGET) lives in
# wrangler.toml [vars]; set here only to override for local dev.

MORSCAN_JWT_SECRET=
MORSCAN_MNEMONIC=
MORSCAN_DEMO_KEY=
MORSCAN_ADMIN_KEY_IDS=
ALCHEMY_FALLBACK_URL=
D1_DAILY_READ_BUDGET=
